_topstories?a=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~4/zhacxDWWwV4\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:29:\"Mon, 20 Jul 2009 13:34:06 EDT\";s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:97:\"http://www.cnn.com/2009/SHOWBIZ/Movies/07/20/spike.lee.right.thing/index.html?eref=rss_topstories\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:1431:\"Surely, columnists warned in 1989, Spike Lee\'s new film  will incite racial unrest. \"This movie is dynamite under every seat,\" one critic wrote. Twenty years later, \"Do the Right Thing\" still maintains a hold on the imagination. But perhaps the real reason people talk about the film is because it\'s still relevant.<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=zhacxDWWwV4:xTfj02zGesI:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/r