http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~4/x3r6xsrdqZg\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:29:\"Mon, 20 Jul 2009 12:49:14 EDT\";s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:90:\"http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/07/20/us.military.increase/index.html?eref=rss_topstories\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:1266:\"Defense Secretary Robert Gates will announce Monday that he plans to increase the size of the military by 20,000 troops, a Pentagon official told CNN.<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=x3r6xsrdqZg:eQtxvDf8HKY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~4/x3r6xsrdqZg\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";}i:2;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Witness to an execution -- more than 315 times\";s:4:\"guid\";s:90:\"http://www.cnn.com/2009/CRIME/07/20/texas.execution.witness/index.html?eref=rss_topstories\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~3/5XmzTt1e7pA/index.html\";s:11:\"description\";s:1441:\"It takes seven minutes to execute a death row inmate, according to the state of Texas. At that rate, Mike Graczyk of The Associated Press has spent about 40 hours of his life watching men -- and a few women -- die. The inmates\' last words stick in his mind. Poetry. Prayers. Bible verses. Curses. One man sang \"Silent Night.\"<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~4/5XmzTt1e7pA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:29:\"Mon, 20 Jul 2009 12:57:55 EDT\";s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:90:\"http://www.cnn.com/2009/CRIME/07/20/texas.execution.witness/index.html?eref=rss_topstories\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:1441:\"It takes seven minutes to execute a death row inmate, according to the state of Texas. At that rate, Mike Graczyk of The Associated Press has spent about 40 hours of his life watching men -- and a few women -- die. The inmates\' last words stick in his mind. Poetry. Prayers. Bible verses. Curses. One man sang \"Silent Night.\"<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=5XmzTt1e7pA:AiVQyrMHtos:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~4/5XmzTt1e7pA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";}i:3;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:42:\"Boy helped grease safe return of Apollo 11\";s:4:\"guid\";s:85:\"http://www.cnn.com/2009/TECH/space/07/20/apollo11.irpt/index.html?eref=rss_topstories\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~3/eXb5RkxuRWo/index.html\";s:11:\"description\";s:1463:\"On July 23, 1969, as Apollo 11 hurtled back toward Earth, there was a problem -- a problem only a kid could solve. Greg Force was living with his family in Guam, where his dad was in charge of a NASA tracking station. When things went wrong with an antenna, it was Greg with a handful of grease and a skinny arm who was able to come to the rescue.<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~4/eXb5RkxuRWo\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:29:\"Mon, 20 Jul 2009 10:52:37 EDT\";s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:85:\"http://www.cnn.com/2009/TECH/space/07/20/apollo11.irpt/index.html?eref=rss_topstories\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:1463:\"On July 23, 1969, as Apollo 11 hurtled back toward Earth, there was a problem -- a problem only a kid could solve. Greg Force was living with his family in Guam, where his dad was in charge of a NASA tracking station. When things went wrong with an antenna, it was Greg with a handful of grease and a skinny arm who was able to come to the rescue.<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?i=eXb5RkxuRWo:OLo4OYbl_wY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~4/eXb5RkxuRWo\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";}i:4;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:45:\"Moon or Mars? \'Next giant leap\' sparks debate\";s:4:\"guid\";s:101:\"http://www.cnn.com/2009/TECH/space/07/20/nasa.future.human.exploration/index.html?eref=rss_topstories\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/cnn_topstories/~3/aQn5o6GGYV0/index.html\";s:11:\"description\";s:1345:\"Blasting off from Earth and hurtling through space at thousands of miles an hour, it takes astronauts three days to reach the moon -- a tiny distance in a universe measured in light years, but a fantastic voyage on a human scale.<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=aQn5o6GGYV0:hl8HMpLJMzU:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?a=aQn5o6GGYV0:hl8HMpLJMzU:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/rss/cnn_topstories?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://rss.cnn.com/~ff/r